WHEREAS On April 2, 2026, Rideau Carleton Raceway announced the conclusion of its harness racing program beginning with the 2026 season, following a decision by Ontario Racing and Hard Rock Hotel & Casino Ottawa;
AND WHEREAS the Raceway has historically played a significant role in supporting Eastern Ontario’s horse racing community, including horse owners, trainers, boarders and associated agricultural and rural businesses;
AND WHEREAS the closure of harness racing operations may have economic and social impacts on Ottawa’s rural communities, including effects on horse boarding operations, feed suppliers, hay producers, veterinarians, farriers, and other ancillary businesses;
AND WHEREAS transitional supports announced by Ontario Racing are primarily focused on relocation and continued racing opportunities elsewhere in the province, and may not fully address local economic impacts within the City of Ottawa;
AND WHEREAS the City of Ottawa has an interest in supporting rural economic development, local agriculture, and small businesses that may be affected by this change;
THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED THAT City Council direct staff to explore the economic impact of the local equine sector as part of the baseline evaluation and benchmark study of Ottawa’s rural economy (Economic Development Rural Plan Recommendation 10);
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT based on the economic impact staff explore and consider viable opportunities, where appropriate, to support the local equine sector, through existing programs, partnerships and economic development initiatives; andBE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT staff report findings back to the Agriculture and Rural Affairs Committee through the planned Rural Plan implementation update in Q1 2027.

That the Rules of Procedure be suspended to consider the following motion at today’s meeting as the matter is time sensitive as the Owner is looking to complete development in the current construction season.
WHEREAS it is a condition of site plan approval for this development that the Owner enter into a Municipal Responsibility Agreement with the City with respect to the private communal water system and the private communal wastewater system servicing the subject property;
AND WHEREAS the said Municipal Responsibility Agreement requires a reserve fund for the operation and maintenance of said private systems;
AND WHEREAS it is a condition of the Owner’s financing that such reserve fund be established through an escrow agreement;
AND WHEREAS the escrow agreement protects the City’s interest with respect to the establishment of the reserve fund;
THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED THAT the General Manager, Infrastructure and Water Services be delegated the authority to enter into an escrow agreement with respect to the reserve fund associated with this development, the terms and conditions of same to be to the satisfaction of the City Solicitor;
AND BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that this motion rise for consideration to the Council meeting of May 13, 2026.
